android.graphics.drawable.Drawable.Callback, android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityEventSource, android.view.KeyEvent.Callback, android.view.ViewManager, android.view.ViewParent, PaymentServerListener
public class DibsPayment
extends android.widget.LinearLayout
implements PaymentServerListener

View to present payment window in.

To use the payment window view:

  • first add it to your layout
  • when the activity that own the view initializes, grab the view by its id, and setup its PaymentResultListener
  • then, call loadPaymentWindow(PaymentData)

See Also:
PaymentResultListener, PaymentData

cancelPayment

public void cancelPayment()
Initiates a cancellation of an ongoing payment.

If the payment window has been fully loaded (a call to PaymentResultListener.paymentWindowLoaded() has been made) and a cancel URL has been set, the cancel URL will be loaded, and the delegate is notified via PaymentResultListener.cancelUrlLoaded() when done loading cancel URL. If no cancel URL has been set, or after cancel URL has been loaded, delegate is notified about the cancel being completed, via a call to PaymentResultListener.paymentCancelled(java.util.Map).

pingResult

public void pingResult(boolean result)
Description copied from interface: PaymentServerListener
Called when a result of payment server access optimization is ready.

NOTE: Receiving false here (or not receiving this callback before app needs to show payment window) is not, in itself, an indicator for not showing the payment window. It "just" means, that no optimal payment server has been found yet. This could happen e.g. if network availability of the mobile device disappears right when optimal server resolution executes.

Specified by:
pingResult in interface PaymentServerListener
Parameters:
result - true if an optimal payment server was found, false otherwise

loadPaymentWindow

public void loadPaymentWindow(PaymentData paymentData)
Initiate loading of payment window with the given payment flow.

The actual loading of the payment window happen asynchronously, hence this method will return before the payment window has been loaded. As a consequence of this, it could be a good idea to pop up some kind of loading indicator, and first remove it again when your PaymentResultListener receives the proper notifications.

Parameters:
paymentData - input to the payment window, that tells it what to show
